    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: April 13, 2026</p>
    <h2>1. Service Description</h2>
    <p>Music System Worker D is a personal content distribution tool that automates the posting of original music content to social media platforms including TikTok, YouTube, and Facebook. This tool is operated by Andrew Liew for the purpose of distributing original music created and owned by the operator.</p>
    <h2>2. Use of Service</h2>
    <p>This application is a personal tool used solely by its owner to distribute original music content. It is not available for public use or third-party access. All content distributed through this service is original work owned by the operator.</p>
    <h2>3. Content Ownership</h2>
    <p>All music content distributed through this service is original work. The operator retains full ownership of all content. No user-generated content from third parties is collected, stored, or distributed.</p>
    <h2>4. Platform Compliance</h2>
    <p>This service operates in compliance with the terms of service and API usage policies of all integrated platforms, including TikTok, YouTube, and Facebook. The service respects rate limits, content policies, and authentication requirements of each platform.</p>
    <h2>5. Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <p>This service is provided as-is for personal use. The operator assumes no liability for platform availability, API changes, or content distribution delays.</p>
    <h2>6. Contact</h2>
    <p>For questions about these terms, contact: activesunandrew@gmail.com</p>
